subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology : the epithet lagonoleucos is an arbitrarily formed word derived from the Greek noun λαγον, meaning “flanks”, and the Greek adjective λευκος, meaning “white”, in reference to the distinctive white sides to the rump of this subspecies. It is to be treated as a noun in apposition [Article 31.2.3 of the Code (
ICZN 1999
)].

newly proposed treatment in a recent treatise on the birds of the Indonesian Archipelago (
Eaton et al . 2016
)
